one shortly after I got out of university.\nhttps://slate.com/human-interest/2023/06/life-before-cell-phones-internet-after-work.html ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/17249/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Software-Engineering","RelPermalink":"/categories/software-engineering/"}],"content":"It\u0026rsquo;s interesting to see how the dynamics of Indian society influence the tech industry globally and it\u0026rsquo;s very useful to learn more about it.\nhttps://restofworld.org/2023/iit-graduates-dominate-tech/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/17247/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Podcast","RelPermalink":"/categories/podcast/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Tooze picks apart Europe\u0026rsquo;s failure (mostly political in nature) to keep up with the United States on a bunch of areas.\nHe also mentions that Germany is debt unconstrained and could borrow much more than it is doing right now to fix its broken infrastructure but won\u0026rsquo;t do it because of stupid politics.\nYour browser does not support the audio element. https://pca.st/y64j6vk4#t=1108.0 ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/fragment-ones-and-tooze-the-united-states-vs-europe/","tags":[],"title":"Fragment Ones and Tooze: The United States vs. Europe"},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Podcast","RelPermalink":"/categories/podcast/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":" Your browser does not support the audio element. Tooze talking for five minutes about the difference between European and American academic traditions. Excuse the low quality but my Wordpress has a 2MB file limit.\nThat is what we were training people to do to write essays which had powerful attack, big full body and a conclusive finish and ideally you\u0026rsquo;d have a student who could make a whole bouquet of different essays across 5-6 exam papers, 3 essays per paper, 15 different essays and what you would want is a student who could really modulate across that range of essay writing types.\nAnd another one:\nThe formula of British economics, French politics and German philosophy is the tried formula for making Marxists and that\u0026rsquo;s basically though that\u0026rsquo;s not my politics that\u0026rsquo;s basically the frame within which I understand comprehensive intellectual engagement with modernity. It requires those three elements:\nYou need to have a sophisticated political grip You need to have a philosophy of history which in the German sense of course comes from Hegel You have to understand capitalism otherwise you\u0026rsquo;re stuck https://pca.st/bv0k67fk#t=639.0 ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/fragment-ones-and-tooze-tooze-unplugged/","tags":[],"title":"Fragment Ones and Tooze: Tooze Unplugged"},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Deutsch","RelPermalink":"/categories/deutsch/"},{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Podcast","RelPermalink":"/categories/podcast/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Once in a while they knock them out of the park in this podcast. In this episode Friedemann Karig goes out and asks for people to understand the necessity and reasons behind violent antifascism in the void left behind when the state fails to protect its citizens.\nYour browser does not support the audio element. https://piratensenderpowerplay.podigee.io/155-neue-episode ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/fragment-piratensender-powerplay-e131-lina-law-order/","tags":[],"title":"Fragment Piratensender Powerplay E131: Lina, Law \u0026amp; Order"},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Deutsch","RelPermalink":"/categories/deutsch/"},{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Putting this receipt here about life in the DDR and its eventual downfall:\nAnekdote 3: im November 89 kam eine neue Schlerin in unsere Klasse. Aus der DDR. Wie ich spter erfuhr, war ihr Vater in einer verantwortlichen Position in einem VEB. Er hat seine Familie in Sicherheit gebracht, weil er Angst hatte, was passiert, wenn alles rauskommt.\nhttps://twitter.com/waldorf _charles/status/1673584970902675456\nIt\u0026rsquo;s anecdata but it\u0026rsquo;s plausible and pretty damning and there\u0026rsquo;s a bunch more where that came from. Don\u0026rsquo;t listen to people glorifying how nice and functional things were under the GDR.\n","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/17234/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Nederlands","RelPermalink":"/categories/nederlands/"},{"LinkTitle":"Podcast","RelPermalink":"/categories/podcast/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Een fragment uit Studio Tegengif \u0026ldquo;#87 Het nieuwe politieke pijnpunt: de Nederlandse vermogensongelijkheid\u0026rdquo; over vermogensongelijkheid en dat belastingen op vastgoed en grond veel te laag zijn.\n","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/fragment-tegengif-87-over-ozb/","tags":[],"title":"Fragment Tegengif 87 over OZB"},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Leadership","RelPermalink":"/categories/leadership/"}],"content":"The multiplier you get working with people who practice rigorous thinking is huge. Most of the work is getting everybody to this point as Wes Kao explains here.\nhttps://www.weskao.com/blog/rigorous-thinking ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/17227/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Product-/-Design","RelPermalink":"/categories/product-/-design/"}],"content":"Some good insights in reading about 