SUV driver knows this, but the car industry themselves have verified that the people who buy those cars are assholes.\nWho has been buying SUVs since automakers turned them into family vehicles? They tend to be people who are insecure and vain. They are frequently nervous about their marriages and uncomfortable about parenthood. They often lack confidence in their driving skills. Above all, they are apt to be self-centered and self-absorbed, with little interest in their neighbors or communities.\nhttps://twitter.com/A _W_Gordon/status/1224385645839253506\n","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15991/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Climate","RelPermalink":"/categories/climate/"},{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"}],"content":"Germany is deeply entrenched in coal as this utterly backward and destructive position by Siemens underlines.\nhttps://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-01-14/siemens-ceo-joe-kaeser-s-odd-defense-of-carmichael-coal-project ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15989/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"New-York","RelPermalink":"/categories/new-york/"}],"content":"A long piece on The Daily which reveals a lot about its inner workings and the all-consuming scale with which something like that operates.\nhttps://nymag.com/intelligencer/2020/01/michael-barbaro-the-daily-podcast-new-york-times.html ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15987/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Nederlands","RelPermalink":"/categories/nederlands/"}],"content":"Ik kijk heel erg uit om dingen op het vernieuwde OneWorld te lezen.\nhttps://www.oneworld.nl/anders/achtergrond/dit-is-het-vernieuwde-oneworld/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15984/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Agile","RelPermalink":"/categories/agile/"},{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"}],"content":"A broad treatment of what the essential quality of Fingerspitzengefhl means.\nhttps://taylorpearson.me/fingerspitzengefuhl/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15982/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Internet","RelPermalink":"/categories/internet/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Venkat keeps churning out these legendary and broadly valid pieces. This one is about why everything online is on fire all the time. Strap in.\nhttps://www.ribbonfarm.com/2020/01/16/the-internet-of-beefs/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15980/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Agile","RelPermalink":"/categories/agile/"},{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Software-Engineering","RelPermalink":"/categories/software-engineering/"}],"content":"A long treatment of how to scale work as organizations grow with some helpful guidelines: Keep the work parallel, the groups small, and the resources local.\nhttps://codahale.com/work-is-work/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15978/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Food","RelPermalink":"/categories/food/"}],"content":"Pizza toast and all kinds of toasties are a staple here with small kids which seems to imply that an odyssey through Japan like Craig Mod undertakes here could be a great idea.\nhttps://www.eater.com/2019/12/16/21003452/japan-kissaten-traditional-cafes-pizza-toast-travel ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15976/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Software-Engineering","RelPermalink":"/categories/software-engineering/"},{"LinkTitle":"Work","RelPermalink":"/categories/work/"}],"content":"I\u0026rsquo;m glad that this takedown of Clean Code by Dan Abramov got so much traction. I have no problem with clean code (lowercase), but inevitably the process of getting there and the things people do as a consequence make the entire endeavor an anti-pattern.\nObsessing with clean codeand removing duplication is a phase many of us go through. When we dont feel confident in our code, it is tempting to attach our sense of self-worth and professional pride to something that can be measured. A set of strict lint rules, a naming schema, a file structure, a lack of duplication.\nAs always, people get too attached to the parts that are the most obvious and the least important.\nhttps://overreacted.io/goodbye-clean-code/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15972/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"London","RelPermalink":"/categories/london/"},{"LinkTitle":"Video","RelPermalink":"/categories/video/"}],"content":" The privilege I have  how? No, genuinely, how?\nWell, I say, in terms of wealth, class, education  that kind of privilege, in knowing how to decode the rules in certain spaces. As a caveat, I add that both of us have privilege, and its not a criticism; I was simply curious to know what she thought. Things take an awkward turn.\nWell no, because, no There is a very long and tense pause, before she insists that, actually, there is little difference between her experience and that of her co-star John Boyega, who grew up in south London to British Nigerian immigrant parents. John grew up on a council estate in Peckham and I think me and him are similar enough that no\u0026hellip; Also, I went to a boarding school for performing arts, which was different.\nDaisy Ridley has no idea that she is privileged.\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/dec/07/daisy-ridley-jj-abrams-star-wars-a-religion ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15970/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Nederlands","RelPermalink":"/categories/nederlands/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":"Een verslag van Marijn Kruk over de bijzonder grimmige politieke situatie in Frankrijk.\nhttps://www.groene.nl/artikel/hoofddoeken-bij-de-fontein ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15968/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Politics","RelPermalink":"/categories/politics/"}],"content":" If I have learned anything from the experience Ive just described, its that the desire to shape, bait, surf, defy, find meaning in, or otherwise control and draw sharp lines between myself and the haters puts me on risky psychic territory. Its dangerous. My provisional conclusion? That the best path for me, should hating on my person ever recur at scale, is to deploy, to the best of my ability, relentless sincerity, credulity, wit, and yes, shamelessness, but, crucially, shameability, tooopenness to being justly shamed. If I become unshameable, after all, what good is my shamelessness? If I start assuming in advance, deep down, that no one whom Ive upset with my words has valid points to make, what will I have become? I found it least harmful, actually, to keep my eyes and ears open throughout the dogpiles, experiencing them as reminders that the revolution will not be content-moderated; that I am fighting for things that make people hate me and that thats sort of okay, I can respect it (plus, hey, its mutual).\nhttps://www.dissentmagazine.org/article/hello-to-my-haters-tucker-carlsons-mob-and-me ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15966/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Leadership","RelPermalink":"/categories/leadership/"},{"LinkTitle":"Product-/-Design","RelPermalink":"/categories/product-/-design/"}],"content":"This is good advice for a Director of UX by Adrian Howard that generalizes well to any other kind of Director.\nhttps://adrianhoward.com/posts/first-steps-director-of-ux/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15962/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Software-Engineering","RelPermalink":"/categories/software-engineering/"}],"content":"A long article by Robert Arkwright that uses react server-side rendering as a hook to discuss various scalability issues.\nhttps://arkwright.github.io/scaling-react-server-side-rendering.html ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15960/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Kids","RelPermalink":"/categories/kids/"},{"LinkTitle":"Reading","RelPermalink":"/categories/reading/"}],"content":"An incredibly sad and beautiful story of a father\u0026rsquo;s last days.\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2019/dec/14/saying-goodbye-to-family-motor-neurone-disease-reflecting-on-end-of-life ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15958/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Reading","RelPermalink":"/categories/reading/"}],"content":"A bit of near-future fiction about crypto as a subsistence work enterprise.\nhttps://logicmag.io/bodies/the-crypto-family-farm/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15956/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"English","RelPermalink":"/categories/english/"},{"LinkTitle":"Software-Engineering","RelPermalink":"/categories/software-engineering/"},{"LinkTitle":"Work","RelPermalink":"/categories/work/"}],"content":"A nice write-up of how Gitlab diagnosed and fixed an outage before it could even happen.\nhttps://about.gitlab.com/blog/2019/11/08/the-consul-outage-that-never-happened/ ","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/blog/15954/","tags":[],"title":""},{"categories":[{"LinkTitle":"Amsterdam","RelPermalink":"/categories/amsterdam/"},{"LinkTitle":"Nederlands","RelPermalink":"/categories/nederlands/"},{"LinkTit